In [[SLASH'EM]] and [[SlashTHEM]], various monsters [[Need +x weapon to hit|require a weapon of a certain enchantment level to be hit]], also known as "enchantment resistance" - accompanying this [[property]] is the ability to [[Hits creatures as +x weapon|hit creatures as a +x weapon]]. Most monsters with this ability are either those that possess significant strength or are magical in some manner.

This property treats the monster's attacks as coming from a weapon of a certain enchantment, with the enchantment specified in the flag within that monster's entry in [[monst.c]] (e.g., <tt>MR_HITASONE</tt>, <tt>MR_HITASTWO</tt> and so on). The property is also intrinsic to monsters with "enchantment resistance": these monsters are not given a specific "hits as" flag, but implicitly hit monsters as the same enchantment of weapon that they resist{{refsrc|mhitm.c|1002|version=SLASH'EM 0.0.7E7F2}} - e.g., the [[Aleax]] has the <tt>MR_PLUSTWO</tt> flag but no <tt>MR_HITAS[[Foo|FOO]]</tt>, so Aleaxes require a +2 weapon or better to hit and hit as +2 weapons themselves.

